name: Proxima Centauri B
description: Proxima Centauri B is an exoplanet orbiting the red dwarf star Proxima Centauri, it is roughly 1.17 times the mass of Earth and there are signs that it lies within its star's habitable zone. [b][color=yellow]LEGENDARY[/color][/b]

name: Proxima Centauri C
description: Proxima Centauri C can be considered as super-Earth or mini-Neptune, with a mass roughly 7 times that of Earth. However the planet is too cold to support liquid water, making it impossible to be habitable. [b][color=yellow]LEGENDARY[/color][/b]

name: Proxima Centauri D
description: Proxima Centauri D is an exoplanet that is the closest to the Solar System. It was found in 2020 so information is scarce, but theoretically possible that Proxima D possesses polar regions with habitable temperatures. [b][color=yellow]LEGENDARY[/color][/b]

description: The Sun is the star at the center of the Solar System. It is a massive, nearly perfect sphere of hot plasma, heated to incandescence by nuclear fusion reactions in its core. It is yet to be formed as a red giant. [b][color=yellow]LEGENDARY[/color][/b]

name: Hydra
description: Hydra is a natural satellite of Pluto, it is the second-largest moon of Pluto, being slightly larger than Nix. [b][color=yellow]LEGENDARY[/color][/b]

name: Callisto

name: Io
description: The most volcanically active body in the Solar System, its surface is a wild canvas of lava lakes and sulfur plains. [b][color=lime]RARE[/color][/b]

name: Europa
description: A bright, icy moon with a vast ocean beneath its surface. Its cracked crust and energy from Jupiter’s pull may support alien life. [b][color=lime]RARE[/color][/b]

name: Amalthea

name: Himalia
description: The largest of Jupiter’s irregular moons, orbiting far from the planet’s equator. It may be a captured asteroid. [b][color=lime]RARE[/color][/b]
